# ✍️ n8n Workflow Publisher
Automatically processes and validates n8n workflow JSON input, sending notifications for failures and success statuses while publishing to GitHub.

---

## Table of Contents
- Overview
- How It Works
- Node Architecture
- Tech Stack
- Prerequisites
- Configuration
- Output
- Edge Cases & Fallbacks

---

## Overview
This workflow is triggered upon form submission, where users paste their n8n workflow JSON. It validates the JSON format and sends notifications based on the validation result.

---

## How It Works
[Connection data unavailable — diagram cannot be generated]
1. The workflow is triggered by the form submission.
2. The JSON input is processed and validated through JavaScript logic.
3. Depending on the success of the validation, either a failure notification is sent via Gmail or a message is sent to an OpenAI model for further processing.

---

## Node Architecture
| Node Name                  | Type                                  | Role                                      |
|---------------------------|---------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| On form submission        | n8n-nodes-base.formTrigger           | Form Trigger                              |
| Code in JavaScript        | n8n-nodes-base.code                  | Processing and validation logic           |
| If                        | n8n-nodes-base.if                    | Conditional branching based on validation  |
| Send a message            | n8n-nodes-base.gmail                 | Sending failure email notification         |
| Message a model           | @n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi      | Interfacing with OpenAI for processing    |

---

## Tech Stack
| Component                 | Technology                               |
|--------------------------|----------------------------------------|
| Form Trigger             | n8n-nodes-base.formTrigger             |
| Code                     | n8n-nodes-base.code                    |
| Conditional Logic        | n8n-nodes-base.if                      |
| Email Notification       | n8n-nodes-base.gmail                   |
| OpenAI Integration       | @n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi        |

---

## Prerequisites
- n8n instance v1.0+
- Gmail OAuth2 API key required
- OpenAI API key required

---

## Configuration
Configure the Gmail and OpenAI API credentials in your n8n instance to ensure this workflow operates correctly.

---

## Output
The workflow provides feedback through emails or integrates with OpenAI, detailing the success or failure of the workflow submission and validation process.

---

## Edge Cases & Fallbacks
| Scenario                                   | Behavior                                                                               |
|-------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Missing required form fields              | The workflow fails to execute and sends an error notification email.                  |
| Malformed workflow JSON input             | A failure email is sent to the user indicating the issue and potential causes.         |
| JSON validation error                     | User receives email notification with instructions for troubleshooting.                 |